          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/By authors/ In the case of 30P, which only gives",
                "rise to annihilation radiation, it was really 2,5 min",
                "30P and not 2.03 min O-15. Therefore, besides gamma-",
                "ray spectroscopy, counting of positrons above 2.0 MeV",
                "/i.e. above the cut-off energy of the positrons from",
                "O-15/ was also applied. Both the counting methods",
                "gave similar results, confirming thereby that the",
                "activity under investigation was pure 30P."
              ]
            }
          ],
